text: Leninsky () is a rural locality (a selo) in Rassvetovsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 358 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Davlekanovo, 22 km from Rassvet. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Leninsky, Davlekanovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
